07/05/2007
ZAGREB, Croatia -- President Stipe Mesic kicks off a two-day official visit to Austria on Monday (May 7th) to meet with counterpart Heinz Fischer, Chancellor Alfred Gusenbauer and Parliament Speaker Barbara Prammer. Talks are expected to focus on bilateral co-operation and EU enlargement issues. Mesic and Gusenbauer will also attend an Austrian-Croatian business forum in Vienna. 
In other news, an EU bus rolled out of Sisak on Saturday, launching a weeklong tour across Croatia as part of a project aimed at getting the public acquainted with the Union. The initiative is especially oriented towards young people. (Poslovni dnevnik, HRT - 07/05/07; Vecernji list - 06/05/07; HINA - 05/05/07)
